TypeSignature.Value: .class public auto ansi sealed JSVsaError extends System.Enum

Attribute.AttributeName: System.Obsolete("Use of this type is not recommended because it is being deprecated in Visual Studio 2005; there will be no replacement for this feature. Please see the ICodeCompiler documentation for additional help.")

Docs.summary: Defines the set of exceptions that can be thrown by a .NET script engine.

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype Microsoft.JScript.Vsa.JSVsaError AppDomainCannotBeSet = int32(-2146226176)
AppDomainCannotBeSet = -2146226176

remarks.format:
## Remarks Exception string: The application domain cannot be set.
Thrown by the <xref:Microsoft.JScript.Vsa.IJSVsaEngine.GetOption*> method or the <xref:Microsoft.JScript.Vsa.IJSVsaEngine.SetOption*> method when attempts fail to set the AppDomain option on a managed engine, such as the Visual Basic or JScript script engines. Managed script engines do not support using custom application domains. Managed script engines will always use the application domain in which they are running.

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype Microsoft.JScript.Vsa.JSVsaError AppDomainInvalid = int32(-2146226175)
AppDomainInvalid = -2146226175

remarks.format:
## Remarks Exception string: The specified application domain is not valid.
Thrown by the <xref:Microsoft.JScript.Vsa.IJSVsaEngine.GetOption*> method or <xref:Microsoft.JScript.Vsa.IJSVsaEngine.SetOption*> method when attempting to set an AppDomain reference that is not valid. To reset the `AppDomain` option to a null reference, call the <xref:Microsoft.JScript.Vsa.IJSVsaEngine.Reset*> method.

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype Microsoft.JScript.Vsa.JSVsaError ApplicationBaseCannotBeSet = int32(-2146226174)
ApplicationBaseCannotBeSet = -2146226174

remarks.format:
## Remarks Exception string: Application base cannot be set.
Thrown by the <xref:Microsoft.JScript.Vsa.IJSVsaEngine.GetOption*> method or <xref:Microsoft.JScript.Vsa.IJSVsaEngine.SetOption*> method when attempts to get or set the ApplicationBase option on a managed engine, such as the Visual Basic .NET or JScript .NET script engines. The host must set the `ApplicationBase` option in the application domain in which it creates its script engine.

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype Microsoft.JScript.Vsa.JSVsaError ApplicationBaseInvalid = int32(-2146226173)
ApplicationBaseInvalid = -2146226173

remarks.format:
## Remarks Exception string: The specified application base directory is not valid.
Thrown by the <xref:Microsoft.JScript.Vsa.IJSVsaEngine.GetOption*> method or <xref:Microsoft.JScript.Vsa.IJSVsaEngine.SetOption*> method when attempts to get or set the ApplicationBase option on an engine, and by the <xref:Microsoft.JScript.Vsa.IJSVsaEngine.Run*> method when the directory specified as the Application Base directory is not a valid directory.

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype Microsoft.JScript.Vsa.JSVsaError AssemblyExpected = int32(-2146226172)
AssemblyExpected = -2146226172

remarks.format:
## Remarks Exception string: <xref:Microsoft.JScript.Vsa.IJSVsaReferenceItem> does not reference a valid assembly.
Thrown by the <xref:Microsoft.JScript.Vsa.IJSVsaEngine.Compile*> method when one of the `IVsaReferenceItem` objects contained in the <xref:Microsoft.JScript.Vsa.IJSVsaItems> collection does not represent a valid assembly.

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype Microsoft.JScript.Vsa.JSVsaError AssemblyNameInvalid = int32(-2146226171)
AssemblyNameInvalid = -2146226171

remarks.format:
## Remarks Exception string: Assembly name is not valid.
Thrown by the <xref:Microsoft.JScript.Vsa.IJSVsaReferenceItem.AssemblyName*> property when an assembly name that is not valid is specified for a <xref:Microsoft.JScript.Vsa.IJSVsaReferenceItem> object.

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype Microsoft.JScript.Vsa.JSVsaError BadAssembly = int32(-2146226170)
BadAssembly = -2146226170

remarks.format:
## Remarks Exception string: Assembly format is not valid.
Thrown when the assembly provided to the engine is not valid. This exception typically occurs when an engine tries to run or use the assembly.

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype Microsoft.JScript.Vsa.JSVsaError BrowserNotExist = int32(-2146226115)
BrowserNotExist = -2146226115

remarks.format:
## Remarks Exception string: The specified browser was not found.
Thrown by the aDTEngine.AttachDebugger method when a remote debugging session has been initiated and an attempt made to launch the remote browser, but a browser is not available.

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype Microsoft.JScript.Vsa.JSVsaError CachedAssemblyInvalid = int32(-2146226169)
CachedAssemblyInvalid = -2146226169

remarks.format:
## Remarks Exception string: The cached assembly is not valid.
Thrown by the <xref:Microsoft.JScript.Vsa.IJSVsaEngine.Run*> method when it is called and it tries to use a previously cached assembly, but the assembly is not valid, for example, it is a null reference (`Nothing` in Visual Basic).

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype Microsoft.JScript.Vsa.JSVsaError CallbackUnexpected = int32(-2146226168)
CallbackUnexpected = -2146226168

remarks.format:
## Remarks Exception string: Callback cannot be made at this time.
Thrown by multiple methods when one of the <xref:Microsoft.JScript.Vsa.IJSVsaSite> or <xref:Microsoft.JScript.Vsa.IJSVsaPersistSite> callback methods is called at an unexpected time. For example, the <xref:Microsoft.JScript.Vsa.IJSVsaSite.GetCompiledState*> method should only be called by an engine as a result of a call to the <xref:Microsoft.JScript.Vsa.IJSVsaEngine.Run*> method. If it is called at any other time, a CallbackUnexpected exception will be thrown.

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype Microsoft.JScript.Vsa.JSVsaError CannotAttachToWebServer = int32(-2146226100)
CannotAttachToWebServer = -2146226100

remarks.format:
## Remarks Exception string: Cannot attach to the specified Web server.
Thrown by the aDTEngine.AttachDebugger method when launching a server-side debugging session and VSA cannot attach the debugger to the specified Web server.

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype Microsoft.JScript.Vsa.JSVsaError CodeDOMNotAvailable = int32(-2146226167)
CodeDOMNotAvailable = -2146226167

remarks.format:
## Remarks Exception string: A valid Code Document Object Model (CodeDOM) is not available.
Thrown by the <xref:Microsoft.JScript.Vsa.IJSVsaCodeItem.CodeDOM*> property when the property is not available to be read. The engine either does not support the property or it requires an explicit call to the <xref:Microsoft.JScript.Vsa.IJSVsaEngine.Compile*> method in order to generate the Document Object Model (DOM).

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype Microsoft.JScript.Vsa.JSVsaError CompiledStateNotFound = int32(-2146226166)
CompiledStateNotFound = -2146226166

remarks.format:
## Remarks Exception string: The specified compiled state could not be loaded.
Thrown by the <xref:Microsoft.JScript.Vsa.IJSVsaSite.GetCompiledState*> method when it is called for an engine that does not have compiled state.

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype Microsoft.JScript.Vsa.JSVsaError DebuggeeNotStarted = int32(-2146226114)
DebuggeeNotStarted = -2146226114

remarks.format:
## Remarks Exception string: Debug target application not started.
Thrown by the aDTEngine.AttachDebugger method when a Windows client debugging session is initiated, but the `AttachDebugger` method is not able to launch the target application that is specified with the TargetEXE option.

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype Microsoft.JScript.Vsa.JSVsaError DebugInfoNotSupported = int32(-2146226165)
DebugInfoNotSupported = -2146226165

remarks.format:
## Remarks Exception string: The use of debug information is not supported.
Thrown by the <xref:Microsoft.JScript.Vsa.IJSVsaEngine.GenerateDebugInfo*> property when it is set to true, but the engine does not support the generation of debugging information. Compilation continues, but the engine compiles code without debug information.

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype Microsoft.JScript.Vsa.JSVsaError ElementNameInvalid = int32(-2146226164)
ElementNameInvalid = -2146226164

remarks.format:
## Remarks Exception string: The element name is not valid.
Thrown by the <xref:Microsoft.JScript.Vsa.IJSVsaPersistSite.LoadElement*> method and <xref:Microsoft.JScript.Vsa.IJSVsaPersistSite.SaveElement*> methods when either is called with a name parameter that is not valid, for example, one that contains characters that are not valid. Note that the host must not throw an ElementNameInvalid Exception when the name parameter is a null pointer, as a null pointer is a valid argument used to request engine-level data.

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype Microsoft.JScript.Vsa.JSVsaError ElementNotFound = int32(-2146226163)
ElementNotFound = -2146226163

remarks.format:
## Remarks Exception string: The element was not found.
Thrown by <xref:Microsoft.JScript.Vsa.IJSVsaPersistSite.LoadElement*> method when it is called with a name parameter that is not valid, that is, one that does not correspond to a previously saved element.

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype Microsoft.JScript.Vsa.JSVsaError EngineBusy = int32(-2146226162)
EngineBusy = -2146226162

remarks.format:
## Remarks Exception string: Engine is busy servicing another thread.
Thrown by all members when an engine is currently servicing a request from another thread. By design, a .NET script engine should only be called from one thread at a time.

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype Microsoft.JScript.Vsa.JSVsaError EngineCannotClose = int32(-2146226161)
EngineCannotClose = -2146226161

remarks.format:
## Remarks Exception string: The specified engine cannot be closed.
Thrown by <xref:Microsoft.JScript.Vsa.IJSVsaEngine.Close*> method when an attempt is made to call this method, but the. NET script engine cannot be closed properly.

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype Microsoft.JScript.Vsa.JSVsaError EngineCannotReset = int32(-2146226160)
EngineCannotReset = -2146226160

remarks.format:
## Remarks Exception string: The specified engine cannot be reset.
Thrown by the <xref:Microsoft.JScript.Vsa.IJSVsaEngine.Reset*> method when it is called, but the .NET script engine could not be reset or its events could not be unhooked.

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype Microsoft.JScript.Vsa.JSVsaError EngineClosed = int32(-2146226159)
EngineClosed = -2146226159

remarks.format:
## Remarks Exception string: Engine has been closed.
Thrown in most cases after the .NET script engine has been closed using a call to the <xref:Microsoft.JScript.Vsa.IJSVsaEngine.Close*> method. Once the Close method has been called, the engine can no longer be used, and a new script engine must be created to perform any tasks.

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype Microsoft.JScript.Vsa.JSVsaError EngineEmpty = int32(-2146226159)
EngineEmpty = -2146226159

remarks.format:
## Remarks Exception string: The specified engine has no source items to compile.
Thrown by the <xref:Microsoft.JScript.Vsa.IJSVsaEngine.Compile*> method when it is called, but there are no items in the <xref:Microsoft.JScript.Vsa.IJSVsaItems> collection to compile, that is, the <xref:Microsoft.JScript.Vsa.IJSVsaItems.Count*> property = 0.

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype Microsoft.JScript.Vsa.JSVsaError EngineInitialized = int32(-2146226157)
EngineInitialized = -2146226157

remarks.format:
## Remarks Exception string: Engine has already been initialized.
Thrown by the <xref:Microsoft.JScript.Vsa.IJSVsaEngine.LoadSourceState*> method and <xref:Microsoft.JScript.Vsa.IJSVsaEngine.InitNew*> methods when these methods are called but the .NET script engine has already been initialized. If the host wants to load source state or initialize a new script engine, the respective methods must be the first ones called after setting the <xref:Microsoft.JScript.Vsa.IJSVsaEngine.RootMoniker* > and <xref:Microsoft.JScript.Vsa.IJSVsaEngine.Site*> properties.

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype Microsoft.JScript.Vsa.JSVsaError EngineNameInUse = int32(-2146226156)
EngineNameInUse = -2146226156

remarks.format:
## Remarks Exception string: The specified engine name is already in use by another engine.
Thrown by <xref:Microsoft.JScript.Vsa.IJSVsaEngine.Name*> property when an attempt is made to set it to the same name as that of an existing .NET script engine inside the host. While the Name property does not need to be globally unique, it cannot be the same as the name of a script engine that is currently being hosted.

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype Microsoft.JScript.Vsa.JSVsaError EngineNameInvalid = int32(-2146226113)
EngineNameInvalid = -2146226113

remarks.format:
## Remarks Exception string: Engine name not valid.
Thrown by the <xref:Microsoft.JScript.Vsa.IJSVsaEngine.Name*> property if the specified name is already in use by another engine. VSA requires that design-time engine names be unique.

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype Microsoft.JScript.Vsa.JSVsaError EngineNameNotSet = int32(-2146226099)
EngineNameNotSet = -2146226099

remarks.format:
## Remarks Exception string: Engine name not valid.
Thrown by the <xref:Microsoft.JScript.Vsa.IJSVsaEngine.Name*> property if the specified name is already in use by another engine. VSA requires that design-time engine names be unique.

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype Microsoft.JScript.Vsa.JSVsaError EngineNotCompiled = int32(-2146226155)
EngineNotCompiled = -2146226155

remarks.format:
## Remarks Exception string: The specified engine is not compiled.
Thrown by the <xref:Microsoft.JScript.Vsa.IJSVsaEngine.Run*> method and <xref:Microsoft.JScript.Vsa.IJSVsaEngine.SaveCompiledState*> methods when there is no compiled state to run or save. Either the .NET script engine must compile the code with a call to the <xref:Microsoft.JScript.Vsa.IJSVsaEngine.Compile*> method, or the <xref:Microsoft.JScript.Vsa.IJSVsaEngine.LoadSourceState*> method must be called before the script engine can be run or saved.

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype Microsoft.JScript.Vsa.JSVsaError EngineNotExist = int32(-2146226112)
EngineNotExist = -2146226112

remarks.format:
## Remarks Exception string: Engine does not exist.
Thrown by the aIDE.ExtensibilityObject property in cases where there are no valid engines from which to retrieve the extensibility object.

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype Microsoft.JScript.Vsa.JSVsaError EngineNotInitialized = int32(-2146226154)
EngineNotInitialized = -2146226154

remarks.format:
## Remarks Exception string: The specified engine has not been initialized.
Thrown by multiple members when the .NET script engine has not been properly initialized, and the host tries to access a property or method that requires the script engine to be initialized.

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype Microsoft.JScript.Vsa.JSVsaError EngineNotRunning = int32(-2146226153)
EngineNotRunning = -2146226153

remarks.format:
## Remarks Exception string: The specified engine must be running.
Thrown by the <xref:Microsoft.JScript.Vsa.IJSVsaEngine.Reset*> method and <xref:Microsoft.JScript.Vsa.IJSVsaEngine.Assembly*> property when either is called and the specified .NET script engine is not running.

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype Microsoft.JScript.Vsa.JSVsaError EngineRunning = int32(-2146226152)
EngineRunning = -2146226152

remarks.format:
## Remarks Exception string: Engine is running.
Thrown by multiple members when the .NET script engine is running, and the host attempts to perform an operation that is not allowed while the script engine is running. For example, attempting to create a new code item using the <xref:Microsoft.JScript.Vsa.IJSVsaItems.CreateItem*> method will produce this exception if the engine is in the running state.

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype Microsoft.JScript.Vsa.JSVsaError EventSourceInvalid = int32(-2146226151)
EventSourceInvalid = -2146226151

remarks.format:
## Remarks Exception string: The specified event source does not exist.
Thrown by the <xref:Microsoft.JScript.Vsa.IJSVsaSite.GetEventSourceInstance*> method when it is called with a parameter or pairing of parameters that is not valid. Either the `itemName` parameter refers to an item that the host did not add to the engine, or the `eventSourceName` parameter refers to an event source that was not added to the specified item.

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype Microsoft.JScript.Vsa.JSVsaError EventSourceNameInUse = int32(-2146226150)
EventSourceNameInUse = -2146226150

remarks.format:
## Remarks Exception string: The specified event source name is already in use.
Thrown by the <xref:Microsoft.JScript.Vsa.IJSVsaCodeItem.AddEventSource*> method when it is called with an `eventSourceName` parameter that has previously been used as an event source name.

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype Microsoft.JScript.Vsa.JSVsaError EventSourceNameInvalid = int32(-2146226149)
EventSourceNameInvalid = -2146226149

remarks.format:
## Remarks Exception string: The specified event source name is not valid.
Thrown by the <xref:Microsoft.JScript.Vsa.IJSVsaCodeItem.AddEventSource*> method and <xref:Microsoft.JScript.Vsa.IJSVsaCodeItem.RemoveEventSource*> methods when either is called with an `eventSourceName` parameter that is not a valid identifier. Hosts can determine whether an identifier is valid by first calling the <xref:Microsoft.JScript.Vsa.IJSVsaEngine> method.

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype Microsoft.JScript.Vsa.JSVsaError EventSourceNotFound = int32(-2146226148)
EventSourceNotFound = -2146226148

remarks.format:
## Remarks Exception string: The specified event source not found.
Thrown by the <xref:Microsoft.JScript.Vsa.IJSVsaCodeItem.RemoveEventSource*> method when it is called with an `eventNameType` parameter that is not already in use as an event source in the code item.

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype Microsoft.JScript.Vsa.JSVsaError EventSourceTypeInvalid = int32(-2146226147)
EventSourceTypeInvalid = -2146226147

remarks.format:
## Remarks Exception string: The specified event source type is not valid.
Thrown by the <xref:Microsoft.JScript.Vsa.IJSVsaCodeItem.AddEventSource*> method when it is called with an `eventSourceType` parameter that is not a valid type. Note that this is not true for the Visual Basic script engine, which instead reports a compile exception in this situation.

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype Microsoft.JScript.Vsa.JSVsaError FileFormatUnsupported = int32(-2146226111)
FileFormatUnsupported = -2146226111

remarks.format:
## Remarks Exception string: File format is not supported.
Reserved for future use.

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype Microsoft.JScript.Vsa.JSVsaError FileTypeUnknown = int32(-2146226110)
FileTypeUnknown = -2146226110

remarks.format:
## Remarks Exception string: File is of unknown type.
Reserved for future use.

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype Microsoft.JScript.Vsa.JSVsaError GetCompiledStateFailed = int32(-2146226146)
GetCompiledStateFailed = -2146226146

remarks.format:
## Remarks Exception string: The specified compiled state could not be loaded.
Thrown by the <xref:Microsoft.JScript.Vsa.IJSVsaSite.GetCompiledState*> method and <xref:Microsoft.JScript.Vsa.IJSVsaEngine.Run*> methods when the `GetCompiledState` method fails. The Run method returns to the caller the `GetCompiledStateFailed` exception returned by the `GetCompiledState` method. The `Run` method may also generate the GetCompiledStateFailed exception if the assembly cache throws an exception.

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype Microsoft.JScript.Vsa.JSVsaError GlobalInstanceInvalid = int32(-2146226145)
GlobalInstanceInvalid = -2146226145

remarks.format:
## Remarks Exception string: The specified global instance does not exist.
Thrown by <xref:Microsoft.JScript.Vsa.IJSVsaSite.GetGlobalInstance*> method when it is called with an invalid name parameter, that is, one that was not added using the <xref:Microsoft.JScript.Vsa.IJSVsaItems.CreateItem*> method.

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype Microsoft.JScript.Vsa.JSVsaError GlobalInstanceTypeInvalid = int32(-2146226144)
GlobalInstanceTypeInvalid = -2146226144

remarks.format:
## Remarks Exception string: Global instance type is not valid.
Thrown when the `TypeString` property of an <xref:Microsoft.JScript.Vsa.IJSVsaGlobalItem> object is not valid.

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype Microsoft.JScript.Vsa.JSVsaError InternalCompilerError = int32(-2146226143)
InternalCompilerError = -2146226143

remarks.format:
## Remarks Exception string: An internal compiler exception has occurred.
Thrown by the <xref:Microsoft.JScript.Vsa.IJSVsaEngine.Compile*> method when it is called and an unexpected exception occurs within the compiler. This exception is not thrown for compilation errors, which are signaled to the host by means of the <xref:Microsoft.JScript.Vsa.IJSVsaSite.OnCompilerError*> method, but for exceptions in the compiler itself.

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype Microsoft.JScript.Vsa.JSVsaError ItemCannotBeRemoved = int32(-2146226142)
ItemCannotBeRemoved = -2146226142

remarks.format:
## Remarks Exception string: The specified item cannot be removed.
Thrown by the <xref:Microsoft.JScript.Vsa.IJSVsaItems.Remove*> and <xref:Microsoft.JScript.Vsa.IJSVsaItems.Remove*> methods when an attempt is made to remove an item that cannot be removed.

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype Microsoft.JScript.Vsa.JSVsaError ItemCannotBeRenamed = int32(-2146226109)
ItemCannotBeRenamed = -2146226109

remarks.format:
## Remarks Exception string: The item cannot be renamed.
Thrown by the <xref:Microsoft.JScript.Vsa.IJSVsaItem.Name*> property in cases where an attempt is made to rename an item that cannot be renamed.

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype Microsoft.JScript.Vsa.JSVsaError ItemFlagNotSupported = int32(-2146226141)
ItemFlagNotSupported = -2146226141

remarks.format:
## Remarks Exception string: The specified flag is not supported.
Thrown by the <xref:Microsoft.JScript.Vsa.IJSVsaItems.CreateItem*> method when the call specifies a flag that is not valid, or a flag that is not supported by the host.

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype Microsoft.JScript.Vsa.JSVsaError ItemNameInUse = int32(-2146226140)
ItemNameInUse = -2146226140

remarks.format:
## Remarks Exception string: The specified item's name is already in use.
Thrown by the <xref:Microsoft.JScript.Vsa.IJSVsaItems.CreateItem*> method and the <xref:Microsoft.JScript.Vsa.IJSVsaItem.Name*> property when a call to the `CreateItem` method is made with a name parameter that is already in use, or when an existing item has its `Name` property set to a name that is already in use.

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype Microsoft.JScript.Vsa.JSVsaError ItemNameInvalid = int32(-2146226139)
ItemNameInvalid = -2146226139

remarks.format:
## Remarks Exception string: Item name is not valid.
Thrown by the <xref:Microsoft.JScript.Vsa.IJSVsaItems.Item*> property when the name of an item is not valid. The name of an item can be set either when calling the `CreateItem` method, or when setting the `Name` property. Use the <xref:Microsoft.JScript.Vsa.IJSVsaEngine> method to determine whether an identifier is valid for the engine.

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype Microsoft.JScript.Vsa.JSVsaError ItemNotFound = int32(-2146226138)
ItemNotFound = -2146226138

remarks.format:
## Remarks Exception string: The specified item not found in the collection.
Thrown by the <xref:Microsoft.JScript.Vsa.IJSVsaItems.Item*> property, <xref:Microsoft.JScript.Vsa.IJSVsaItems.Remove*> method, <xref:Microsoft.JScript.Vsa.IJSVsaItems.Item*> property, and <xref:Microsoft.JScript.Vsa.IJSVsaItems.Remove*> method when the aItems.Item property is indexed using a parameter that is not valid. When using the string overload, the name parameter must be the same as the name of an item already in the collection; when using the int overload, the `index` parameter must be between 0 and the value of the <xref:Microsoft.JScript.Vsa.IJSVsaItems.Count*> property -1, inclusive.

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype Microsoft.JScript.Vsa.JSVsaError ItemTypeNotSupported = int32(-2146226137)
ItemTypeNotSupported = -2146226137

remarks.format:
## Remarks Exception string: The specified item type is not supported.
Thrown by the <xref:Microsoft.JScript.Vsa.IJSVsaItems.CreateItem*> method when a call is made with an `itemType` parameter that is not supported by the engine. Note that not all engines support all the values of the VsaItemType enumeration.

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype Microsoft.JScript.Vsa.JSVsaError LCIDNotSupported = int32(-2146226136)
LCIDNotSupported = -2146226136

remarks.format:
## Remarks Exception string: The specified locale identifier (LCID) is not supported.
Thrown by the <xref:Microsoft.JScript.Vsa.IJSVsaEngine.LCID*> property when it is set to an LCID that is not supported by the engine.

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype Microsoft.JScript.Vsa.JSVsaError LoadElementFailed = int32(-2146226135)
LoadElementFailed = -2146226135

remarks.format:
## Remarks Exception string: The specified element could not be loaded.

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype Microsoft.JScript.Vsa.JSVsaError MissingPdb = int32(-2146226102)
MissingPdb = -2146226102

remarks.format:
## Remarks Exception string: n/a
Reserved for future use.

MissingSource = -2146226108

remarks.format:
## Remarks Exception string: Missing source.
Reserved for future use.

NameTooLong = -2146226106

remarks.format:
## Remarks Exception string: The engine name exceeds the allowable length of 256 characters.
Thrown by the <xref:Microsoft.JScript.Vsa.IJSVsaEngine.Name*> property in cases where the value set for the engine name exceeds 256 characters.

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype Microsoft.JScript.Vsa.JSVsaError NotClientSideAndNoUrl = int32(-2146226101)
NotClientSideAndNoUrl = -2146226101

remarks.format:
## Remarks Exception string: n/a
Reserved for future use.

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype Microsoft.JScript.Vsa.JSVsaError NotificationInvalid = int32(-2146226134)
NotificationInvalid = -2146226134

remarks.format:
## Remarks Exception string: The specified notification is not valid.
Thrown by the <xref:Microsoft.JScript.Vsa.IJSVsaSite.Notify*> method when it is called with a notification that is not valid. It is generally recommended that host applications ignore notifications of which they are not aware, or to which they do not need to respond. However, in cases where they do handle a specific notification and the notification is not valid, hosts should throw the NotificationInvalid exception.

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype Microsoft.JScript.Vsa.JSVsaError NotInitCompleted = int32(-2146226107)
NotInitCompleted = -2146226107

remarks.format:
## Remarks Exception string: The aDTEngine.InitCompleted method has not been called.
Thrown by the aDTEngine.GetIDE method or by the signTime.ShowIDE method in cases where either is called before the `InitCompleted` method has been called, signaling that initialization is complete.
